{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Maximum Likelihood Estimation\n\nFit probability distribution parameters by maximizing likelihood (equivalently, minimizing negative log-likelihood). The **symbolic-numeric bridge** shines: we write the log-likelihood symbolically, derive the score function (gradient) with `diff()`, then optimize numerically with `np_minimize`.\n\n1. **Normal distribution** [S+N] — closed-form MLE as benchmark\n2. **Gamma distribution** [S+N] — no closed form, requires optimization\n3. **Fisher information** [S+N] — confidence intervals from the Hessian\n4. **Logistic regression** [S+N] — GLM with symbolic link function",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"numerics-optimize\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 1. Normal Distribution MLE [S+N]\n\n### Symbolic Phase: Log-Likelihood and Score\n\nFor i.i.d. $X_i \\sim \\mathcal{N}(\\mu, \\sigma^2)$, the per-observation log-likelihood is\n$$\\ell_i(\\mu, \\sigma) = -\\ln\\sigma - \\frac{(x_i - \\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2}$$\n\nThe score function (gradient of $\\ell$) gives the MLE in closed form.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Per-observation log-likelihood */\nll_i(mu, sigma, x_i) := -log(sigma) - (x_i - mu)^2 / (2 * sigma^2)$\n\n/* Score function: derivatives of ll_i */\nscore_mu : diff(ll_i(mu, sigma, x[i]), mu);\nscore_sigma : diff(ll_i(mu, sigma, x[i]), sigma);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 15,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "(x[i]-mu)/sigma^2"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "{{\\left(x_{i}-\\mu\\right)^2}\\over{\\sigma^3}}-{{1}\\over{\\sigma}}"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 15,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Setting the score to zero:\n- $\\hat{\\mu} = \\bar{x}$ (sample mean)\n- $\\hat{\\sigma}^2 = \\frac{1}{n}\\sum(x_i - \\bar{x})^2$ (MLE uses $n$, not $n-1$)\n\nWe verify that `np_minimize` finds the same solution.\n\n### Numeric Phase: Closed-Form vs Optimization",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Generate data from N(3, 2^2) */\nn_norm : 200$\ndata_norm : np_add(3.0, np_scale(2.0, np_randn([n_norm])))$\n\n/* Closed-form MLE */\nmu_cf : np_mean(data_norm)$\nsigma_cf : sqrt(np_mean(np_pow(np_sub(data_norm, mu_cf), 2)))$\nprint(\"Closed-form: mu =\", mu_cf, \", sigma =\", sigma_cf)$\n\n/* Numeric MLE via np_minimize (minimize negative log-likelihood) */\n/* We optimize [mu, log(sigma)] to keep sigma > 0 */\nnll_norm(p) := block([mu_v, sig_v],\n  mu_v : np_ref(p, 0),\n  sig_v : exp(np_ref(p, 1)),\n  n_norm * log(sig_v)\n    + np_sum(np_pow(np_sub(data_norm, mu_v), 2)) / (2 * sig_v^2))$\n\nnll_norm_grad(p) := block([mu_v, log_sig, sig_v, res],\n  mu_v : np_ref(p, 0),\n  log_sig : np_ref(p, 1),\n  sig_v : exp(log_sig),\n  res : np_sub(data_norm, mu_v),\n  ndarray([\n    -np_sum(res) / sig_v^2,\n    n_norm - np_sum(np_pow(res, 2)) / sig_v^2  /* chain rule: d/d(log_sig) */\n  ]))$\n\n[p_norm, _, _] : np_minimize(nll_norm, nll_norm_grad, ndarray([0.0, 0.0]))$\nprint(\"np_minimize: mu =\", np_ref(p_norm, 0),\n      \", sigma =\", exp(np_ref(p_norm, 1)))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 16,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Closed-form: mu = 2.780627013714442 , sigma = 2.0905371415544867\n*************************************************\n  N=    2   NUMBER OF CORRECTIONS= 2\n       INITIAL VALUES\n F=  1.210223212961730D+03   GNORM=  2.289029880532844D+03\n*************************************************\n   I  NFN     FUNC                    GNORM                   STEPLENGTH\n   1    2     3.493417214207001D+02   1.325372038628683D+02   4.368662936663886D-04\n  14   18     2.474842076969837D+02   2.021309684523029D-08   1.000000000000000D+00\n THE MINIMIZATION TERMINATED WITHOUT DETECTING ERRORS.\n IFLAG = 0\nnp_minimize: mu = 2.780627013857002 , sigma = 2.090537141654473"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "mu_fit : np_ref(p_norm, 0)$\nsig_fit : exp(np_ref(p_norm, 1))$\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"steelblue\",\n  ax_histogram(np_to_list(data_norm)),\n  title=\"Normal MLE: Histogram of Data\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"Count\", grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 17,
